special_powers.name: SLO-MO BULLET TIME!
special_powers.description: Deadpool, Merc with a Mouth makes a range attack using [Improved Targeting: Characters, Hindering, Adjacent)], targeting each opposing character within range and line of fire. Each hit character is dealt 2 penetrating damage instead of normal damage. Deadpool, Merc with a Mouth can use Probability Control during this attack.

special_powers.name: DO YOU SEE THE COMIC PANELS TELLING ME WHAT TO DO?
special_powers.description: At the beginning of your turn, if D.E.A.D.P.O.O.L. has no action tokens, you may attach a comic panel to him, removing an already attached one. He can use the listed effect.

special_powers.name: DESTRICTIVE ENGINE OF ASSASSINATION DESPITE... AWW, JUST LOOK AT MY REAL NAME
special_powers.description: D.E.A.D.P.O.O.L. can't use the Carry ability. When D.E.A.D.P.O.O.L. makes a close attack and actions resolve, he may make a ranged attack with Improved Targeting: Adjacent.

special_powers.name: FREEDOM AUGMENTING ROCKET TRANSPORTATION SYSTEM
special_powers.description: D.E.A.D.P.O.O.L. can use Charge and Sidestep. When he uses Sidestep and actions resolve he may use Smoke Cloud as a free action, but only to place hindering terrain markers in squares he moved through.

special_powers.name: Enhancement
special_powers.description: The unit to which the comic panel is attached can use the listed effect.

special_powers.name: DO YOU SEE THE COMIC PANELS TELLING ME WHAT TO DO?
special_powers.description: At the beginning of your turn, if Championpool has no action tokens, you may attach a Comic Panel to him, removing any already attached. He can use the listed effect.

special_powers.name: I WILL NOT FALL FOR YOUR TRICKS YET AGAIN!
special_powers.description: Championpool's combat values can't be decreased below their printed values.

special_powers.name: I FIGHT BETTER ALONE!
special_powers.description: If Championpool makes the first attack of the turn, modify his attack value by +1. When he does, you may modify his damage value by +1 but if you do, no other friendly characters may attack this turn.

special_powers.name: Combat Reflexes
special_powers.description: The unit to which the comic panel is attached can use the listed effect.

special_powers.name: STAND BACK, CITIZEN!
special_powers.description: Golden Age Deadpool can use Defend. Golden Age Deadpool can use the Carry ability, but only to carry up to two friendly characters with lower point values.

special_powers.name: DO YOU SEE THE COMIC PANELS TELLING ME WHAT TO DO?
special_powers.description: At the beginning of your turn, if Golden Age Deadpool has no action tokens, you may attach a comic panel to him, removing an already attached one. He can use the listed effect.

special_powers.name: Smoke Cloud
special_powers.description: The unit to which the comic panel is attached can use the listed effect.

special_powers.name: SMASH WELL-DEVELOPED SENSE OF IRONY!
special_powers.description: When Hulkpool hits a single opposing character with a close attack and his attack total is at least 4 greater than the target's defense value, after actions resolve choose one: heal Hulkpool 3 clicks, or counter all powers on the hit character.

special_powers.name: DO YOU SEE THE COMIC PANELS TELLING ME WHAT TO DO?
special_powers.description: At the beginning of your turn, if Hulkpool has no action tokens, you may attach a comic panel to him, removing an already attached one. He can use the listed effect.

special_powers.name: REVERT: DEADPOOL
special_powers.description: Give Hulkpool a free action and replace him with a character named Deadpool of equal or less points on the same click number -1. That character cannot be replaced.

special_powers.name: Quake
special_powers.description: The unit to which the comic panel is attached can use the listed effect.

special_powers.name: BOB, YOU'LL BE MY PARROT
special_powers.description: Other friendly characters have the Pirate keyword. At the beginning of the game, place adjacent a Parrot Bob bystander.

special_powers.name: DO YOU SEE THE COMIC PANELS TELLING ME WHAT TO DO?
special_powers.description: At the beginning of your turn, if Pirate Deadpool has no action tokens, you may attach a comic panel to him, removing an already attached one. He can use the listed effect.

special_powers.name: MY SOLID GOLD GUN WITH DIAMOND BULLETS - "THE COMPENSATOR"
special_powers.description: Pirate Deadpool can use Penetrating/Psychic Blast. When he does, replace his attack value with the highest attack value from all characters on the map.

special_powers.name: Energy Shield/Deflection
special_powers.description: The unit to which the comic panel is attached can use the listed effect.

special_powers.name: DO YOU SEE THE COMIC PANELS TELLING ME WHAT TO DO?
special_powers.description: At the beginning of your turn, if Pool Captain has no action tokens, you may attach a comic panel to him, removing an already attached one. He can use the listed effect.

special_powers.name: Precision Strike
special_powers.description: The unit to which the comic panel is attached can use the listed effect.

special_powers.name: DO YOU SEE THE COMIC PANELS TELLING ME WHAT TO DO?
special_powers.description: At the beginning of your turn, if Pulp Deadpool has no action tokens, you may attach a comic panel to him, removing an already attached one. He can use the listed effect.

special_powers.name: FIFTY AGAINST ONE, NOT BAD
special_powers.description: Pulp Deadpool can use Charge, Plasticity and Running Shot.

special_powers.name: Stealth
special_powers.description: The unit to which the comic panel is attached can use the listed effect.

special_powers.name: DO YOU SEE THE COMIC PANELS TELLING ME WHAT TO DO?
special_powers.description: At the beginning of your turn, if Venompool has no action tokens, you may attach a comic panel to him, removing an already attached one. He can use the listed effect.

special_powers.name: RETCON EXPONGIFIER GUN
special_powers.description: When an opposing character uses Probability Control, after actions resolve, that character cannot use Probability Control for the rest of the game.

special_powers.name: + Target
special_powers.description: The unit to which the comic panel is attached can use the listed effect.

special_powers.name: THAT HORN JUST AIN'T FOR SHOW
special_powers.description: At the beginning of your turn, if Deadpool has no action tokens, he can make a close attack using Blades/Claws/Fangs.

special_powers.name: I'M HERE TO SPREAD JOY AND RAINBOWS
special_powers.description: I'm Here To Spread Joy And Rainbows: When Deadpool hits an opposing character, after actions resolve, you can place the Rainbow Joy Marker on that character, removing it from anywhere else. A character with a Rainbow Joy Marker cannot attack Deadpool unless it is the only character on its force. At the beginning of its player's turn, a character with a Rainbow Joy Marker can roll a d6: on a result of 5 or 6, they may remove the Rainbow Joy Marker.

special_powers.name: YOU HAVE NEVER SEEN ANYTHING SO AWESOME
special_powers.description: Deadpool can use Impervious. Once per game, when Deadpool would take damage, you may choose that he takes no damage instead.

special_powers.name: HE WON'T BE NEEDING IT
special_powers.description: When an adjacent standard character is KO'd, choose a standard power that character could use on any click. Terror can use that power this game.

special_powers.name: DOES EVERYONE ON THIS TEAM HAVE A HEALING FACTOR?
special_powers.description: Terror can use Toughness and can use Regeneration with minimum result 1.

special_powers.name: COLOR-COORDINATED
special_powers.description: Terror can use Outwit, but only to counter pink powers.

special_powers.name: Yellow Dashed Line
special_powers.description: This line separates the two levels. A trap door needs to be used to move between the two levels.

special_powers.name: Orange Numbers
special_powers.description: These mark the trapdoors. Characters using trapdoors must enter and exit with a trapdoor with the same number.

special_powers.name: Open Air Terrain
special_powers.description: If a character that can't use Leap/Climb, Phasing/Teleport, Flight or Great Size occupies Open Air Terrain after actions resolve, deal that character 1 unavoidable damage and then the character's controller places the character in their starting area.
